<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %> | Josiah Tayi</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
<header>
    <h1>Welcome, I'm <%= name %></h1>
    <nav>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/projects">Projects</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>

    </nav>
</header>
<section class="about-me">
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>Full-stack developer and recent RMIT IT graduate who has built and shipped production web applications end-to-end
        — front-end, back-end APIs, role-based authentication, payments, and relational databases. Strong in TypeScript
        on the Next.js/Node.js stack with PostgreSQL, Azure-certified (AZ-900), and comfortable in Linux and
        containerised environments. Motivated by solving practical, commercial problems in a collaborative,
        cross-functional team.</p>
</section>

<section class="experience">
    <h2>Experience</h2>

    <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
            <h3>Full-Stack Developer</h3>
            <span class="date">2026</span>
        </div>
        <p class="company">FinSeeker.com.au</p>
        <p class="experience-desc">B2B commercial-lending matchmaking platform connecting Australian finance seekers with lender Business Development Managers.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Designed and implemented a dual-portal architecture (seeker portal + lender dashboard) with role-based auth using Better Auth and magic-link email flows.</li>
            <li>Integrated Supabase Realtime for live chat between seekers and lenders, enabling deal qualification before identity disclosure.</li>
            <li>Built a Stripe subscription and credit-purchase system for lender access tiers, including webhook handling for lifecycle events.</li>
            <li>Delivered transactional email notifications (pitch received, connection accepted, message digest) via Resend.</li>
            <li>Covered 15+ commercial finance categories and 8 security types with a type-matched lender notification system.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="stack"><strong>Stack:</strong> Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Drizzle ORM, Supabase, Vercel</p>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
            <h3>Software Development Intern</h3>
            <span class="date">2025</span>
        </div>
        <p class="company">Vision Verse Interactive</p>
        <p class="experience-desc">Quiz Builder Platform — a full-stack quiz creation and analytics product.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Built a full-stack quiz creation and analytics platform with a drag-and-drop builder, supporting multiple scoring systems and reusable page templates.</li>
            <li>Architected a JSONB-based quiz schema in PostgreSQL using Drizzle ORM, enabling flexible quiz structures with draft/publish versioning and participant response tracking.</li>
            <li>Integrated Clerk (Google OAuth) for authentication and UploadThing for media uploads, enabling shareable quiz links with no participant registration required.</li>
            <li>Implemented a real-time analytics dashboard with Recharts for visualising quiz performance, device breakdowns, and participant response data.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="stack"><strong>Stack:</strong> Next.js, TypeScript, PostgreSQL (Neon), Drizzle ORM, Clerk, Tailwind CSS, Vercel</p>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
            <h3>IT Support Intern</h3>
            <span class="date">2024</span>
        </div>
        <p class="company">The Midlands Private Hospital</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Delivered Level 1/2 technical support in a clinical environment, logging and resolving tickets in ServiceNow.</li>
            <li>Administered user accounts, access and devices via Active Directory and Microsoft 365.</li>
            <li>Communicated clearly with non-technical staff to diagnose issues and minimise disruption to care delivery.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="education">
    <h2>Education</h2>
    <div class="education-tag">
        <h3>Bachelor of Information Technology</h3>
        <p class="school">RMIT University</p>
        <p class="date">Graduated 2025</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Relevant Coursework: Programming 1 &amp; 2, Web Programming, Database Concepts, Software Engineering
                Fundamentals, Data Communications, Professional Computing Practice, Security in Computing and IT
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="coursework">
    <h2>Technical Skills</h2>

    <div class="skill-category">
        <h3>Languages</h3>
        <p>TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, SQL, HTML/CSS, Bash</p>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-category">
        <h3>Frameworks &amp; Libraries</h3>
        <p>Next.js (App Router), React, Node.js, Tailwind CSS, Recharts</p>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-category">
        <h3>Databases &amp; ORM</h3>
        <p>PostgreSQL (Supabase, Neon), Drizzle ORM, MongoDB</p>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-category">
        <h3>Cloud &amp; DevOps</h3>
        <p>Microsoft Azure (AZ-900), Vercel CI/CD, Docker, Git, Linux</p>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-category">
        <h3>Integrations &amp; Practices</h3>
        <p>Stripe, Clerk, Better Auth, Resend, UploadThing, REST APIs, Agile</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="extracurricular">
    <h2>Extracurricular Activities</h2>

    <div class="activity-item">
        <h3>Africans at RMIT Secretary</h3>
        <p class="date">2023 - 2024</p>
        <p>Organised multiple events and gatherings, collaborating with peers and outside institutions.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="certifications">
    <h2>Certifications</h2>
    <ul class="cert-list">
        <li>Microsoft Certified: Azure Fundamentals (AZ-900)</li>
        <li>Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA)</li>
        <li>CompTIA A+</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2025 Josiah Tayi</p>
    <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/projects">Projects</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
    </div>
</footer>
</body>
</html>
